1
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,667
This is all your son's fault!

2
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,567
It's your fault!

3
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:21,700
Because you're a pest!

4
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:22,967
I want to kill you!

5
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:26,233
But it won't heal my daughter!

6
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:29,600
If she's going to die,
she should leave my son alone!

7
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,733
She can go straight to hell!

8
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:33,267
You're so evil!

9
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,933
You're a horrible person!

10
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:36,700
I heard these two are lovers.

11
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:39,133
But their families
hate each other.

12
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:41,167
That's why they ran away.

13
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:43,467
They must love each other
so much.

14
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:45,933
That's why they did everything
to fight for it.

15
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:50,300
My God!

16
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:59,400
We're in the place
where everything started.

17
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:01,067
We're free here.

18
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,067
We're free to love each other.

19
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,967
But what about the people
we love?

20
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,267
What about my mom?

21
00:01:07,433 --> 00:01:10,133
Please forgive me.

22
00:01:10,267 --> 00:01:12,867
I'm begging you.

23
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Not my child, please.

24
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:18,733
Your mom and your dad.

25
00:01:18,867 --> 00:01:22,167
I'm sure they will get hurt
if they lose us.

26
00:01:22,300 --> 00:01:24,667
Victor, what's going on?

27
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:26,300
Is it going to happen again?

28
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:28,033
Are we going to lose our son
again?

29
00:01:28,167 --> 00:01:30,000
Victor, I can't bear
to lose him!

30
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,467
You should have thought
about that

31
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,533
while Red is still with us.

32
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:36,267
I wish you didn't let hatred
and revenge take over you.

33
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:40,667
Your war with Amanda
could have been over by now.

34
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:42,633
God, please,
I will change my ways.

35
00:01:43,667 --> 00:01:45,467
I will fix my life.

36
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:49,833
I will give her
everything Eden wants.

37
00:01:49,967 --> 00:01:52,567
I can't lose her.

38
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:58,700
I will let go of all my hatred.

39
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:03,467
Amanda's daughter deserves
to die, not our son!

40
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:07,100
Because the love
we have for each other

41
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:13,467
is our weapon to whatever
life may throw at us.

42
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:14,867
I trust you.

43
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,400
They both flatlined.

44
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:21,700
And they both got revived.

45
00:02:21,833 --> 00:02:22,700
I can't explain it.

46
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:24,833
It seems like
they are connected.

47
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:26,467
Stop looking for Red.

48
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:27,533
He's in the hospital.

49
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:29,800
Thank your stars
that my son is alive.

50
00:02:29,933 --> 00:02:32,100
All your evil plans
against Amanda

51
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:33,900
have backfired on you!

52
00:02:34,033 --> 00:02:35,633
Maybe Rina is right.

53
00:02:35,767 --> 00:02:37,300
This is all my fault.

54
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,867
Dindi is right.

55
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:43,267
I shouldn't have gotten
between you and Red.

56
00:03:01,567 --> 00:03:03,867
I won't let my anger
take over anymore.

57
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,133
I'll put everything behind me,
Eden.

58
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:11,367
I won't stand
between you and Red anymore.

59
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,733
I won't stop you
from loving him.

60
00:03:22,733 --> 00:03:25,933
It's okay if you don't want
to stay with me.

61
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:33,400
I will love you from afar.

62
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,133
As long as you're alive.

63
00:03:39,233 --> 00:03:41,600
I love you so much, Eden.

64
00:03:58,033 --> 00:03:59,367
Eden.

65
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,633
Eden.

66
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:08,067
Thank God.

67
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,333
I want to see Yenyen.

68
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,000
Red!

69
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:22,133
Of course, Son.

70
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:23,300
You can see Yenyen.

71
00:04:23,433 --> 00:04:26,033
But you have to get better
first.

72
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,467
Come on, Red.
You're not even well yet.

73
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:31,133
And you want to see Eden
already?

74
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:32,600
Come on, just for once,

75
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:34,067
- please.
- The car brake didn't work,

76
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,200
Dad.

77
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:39,000
What do you mean
the brake didn't work?

78
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,067
That's the reason
we got in an accident.

79
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:46,000
Because the car brake
didn't work.

80
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:49,867
We had an accident because...

81
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:53,667
I forced Yenyen to run away
with me.

82
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:57,567
I tried to get her
away from her mom.

83
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,000
Dad, it's all my fault.

84
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,567
- No, no, no.
- It's my fault.

85
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:04,733
- No, no, Red.
- It's my fault.

86
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:06,700
No, Red.

87
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:08,267
Don't blame yourself.

88
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:13,733
If the car brake fails to work,
it's a mechanical failure.

89
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,100
It's not your fault.

90
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:29,467
She's doing good.

91
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:30,633
Actually,
she's doing more than good.

92
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:31,700
She's doing great!

93
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:33,267
If she keeps this up,

94
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,733
we can actually have her
discharged as early as...

95
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:39,533
maybe tomorrow. But we still
need to run a few more tests.

96
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:42,467
If she passes those,
then I can have her discharged.

97
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,000
Okay, thank you, Doctor.

98
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,167
Thank you so much.

99
00:05:47,233 --> 00:05:48,333
You heard that, right?

100
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:54,133
Get your strength back,
so you can get better.

101
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:58,000
Your Aunt Dindi
can't visit you now

102
00:05:58,133 --> 00:05:59,133
because...

103
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:03,033
her fake illness
has become real.

104
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:06,800
You think it's funny?

105
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:07,933
Mom.

106
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:12,467
Mom, how's Red?

107
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,867
It's like a miracle happened.

108
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,867
They both flatlined.

109
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,733
But both of them got revived.

110
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:25,500
I can't explain it. It seems
like they are connected.

111
00:06:29,033 --> 00:06:31,733
Don't worry about Red.

112
00:06:31,867 --> 00:06:33,033
He's safe.

113
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:36,333
Just like you, he's been
transferred to a private room.

114
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,167
Don't worry about him right now,
okay?

115
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:48,400
Focus on yourself first.

116
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:52,133
Get your strength back,
and once you're recovered,

117
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:54,800
you can see him.

118
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:57,500
I won't stand
between you two again.

119
00:07:00,167 --> 00:07:01,867
Mom, are you serious?

120
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:05,933
Eden, please forgive me.

121
00:07:07,767 --> 00:07:10,100
Forgive me for everything
I've done.

122
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,867
Mom, I'm sorry too.

123
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,533
I made you worry.

124
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:27,533
I'm sorry for choosing Red
over you.

125
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:30,567
I thought you wouldn't accept
our relationship.

126
00:07:32,867 --> 00:07:34,200
Let's put that behind us now.

127
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,900
Let's start over again.

128
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:42,267
And because you love Red
so much,

129
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,567
I can now accept it.

130
00:07:50,533 --> 00:07:55,133
Because I want to see you happy.

131
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,433
Because I want...

132
00:07:58,067 --> 00:08:01,067
Your happiness means a lot
to me.

133
00:08:04,733 --> 00:08:05,833
Thank you, Mom.

134
00:08:32,567 --> 00:08:33,600
Hi.

135
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,667
Can I join you?

136
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,200
Of course.

137
00:09:39,767 --> 00:09:40,733
Come in.

138
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:48,500
How's Eden doing?

139
00:09:48,633 --> 00:09:50,200
She's getting some rest.

140
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:53,900
She's doing better now.

141
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,367
I know you have a lot
on your mind...

142
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,667
And I don't want to bother you.

143
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,900
You need to know something.

144
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,033
What is it?

145
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,900
The investigators
just informed me.

146
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:18,067
They found out
the car's brake line was broken,

147
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:20,300
- which caused their accident.
- What?

148
00:10:20,433 --> 00:10:21,400
Looks like someone did it
on purpose.

149
00:10:21,533 --> 00:10:22,533
What?

150
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:26,200
Eden and Red
were not the targets.

151
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:31,867
It's just a coincidence
that they took the car.

152
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,300
You were the target, Amanda.

153
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:37,600
The kids just got involved.

154
00:10:39,533 --> 00:10:40,767
Who would do that?

155
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,767
When I got the result
of the investigation,

156
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:50,500
I immediately asked
for the footage.

157
00:10:53,967 --> 00:10:55,767
This is the answer
to all your questions.

158
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:07,900
It's Zandro.

159
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:35,933
Zandro.

160
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:47,800
He's the one we need
to put Rina in jail.

161
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:50,933
We will make him sing.

162
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:54,033
So we can get Rina back to jail.

163
00:11:55,867 --> 00:11:57,367
He's all yours, Amanda.

164
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,033
Wake him up.

165
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:03,167
Hey.

166
00:12:10,967 --> 00:12:12,267
You probably thought

167
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,567
you could hide from us forever

168
00:12:15,733 --> 00:12:17,167
after everything you and Rina
have done.

169
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:21,767
Especially now
that you've hurt Eden too.

170
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,467
I don't know
what you're talking about.

171
00:12:29,767 --> 00:12:30,767
Make him remember.

172
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:32,967
He's so stubborn.

173
00:12:35,967 --> 00:12:37,133
Sing!

174
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:38,267
You're all a bastard!

175
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:42,033
Maybe he doesn't know
his lyrics yet.

176
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:43,167
One more.

177
00:12:48,233 --> 00:12:49,867
- What now?
- That's enough!

178
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:55,600
We all know Rina told him
to cut the car's brake line.

179
00:12:56,767 --> 00:12:58,500
You don't need to hurt him.

180
00:12:58,633 --> 00:13:00,667
I don't know
what you're talking about.

181
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,133
You have some nerves.

182
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:06,600
Here.

183
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:10,833
How can you explain this?

184
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:20,033
Rina, I did what you asked me
to do.

185
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,933
I cut the brake line
of Lucho's car.

186
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,633
It's all in the bag, Rina.

187
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:25,500
I messed with his car's
brake line.

188
00:13:25,633 --> 00:13:28,833
He won't notice it at first.

189
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:30,800
But once he starts driving
faster,

190
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:33,300
the brake fluid
will get drained.

191
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:36,200
I'm sure his brake won't work
once they get faster.

192
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,300
Once I give this
to the police officers,

193
00:13:40,433 --> 00:13:41,867
you will rot in jail.

194
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,200
So you will suffer alone

195
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:47,500
while she's out there
living her life.

196
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:51,233
You always mess things up
for me!

197
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,833
I didn't mess up, Rina.

198
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,833
You couldn't control Red!

199
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:03,467
Your evil plans against Amanda
have backfired on you!

200
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,067
And now you're blaming me
for it?

201
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:16,133
How many times did Rina
abandon you?

202
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:18,033
Do you think she won't do it
again?

203
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:22,433
Your sister is just using you.

204
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:27,400
Are you going to let her
get away with this?

205
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:40,667
Eden,

206
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:44,100
I'm so happy you're safe
from the car accident.

207
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:46,467
But I'm overjoyed

208
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,400
because your mom
finally accepted

209
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:50,000
your relationship with Red.

210
00:14:50,133 --> 00:14:51,233
I hope she's serious.

211
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:52,867
It's real.

212
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,467
I felt her sincerity.

213
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:58,167
And after everything
that happened,

214
00:14:58,300 --> 00:15:01,900
I think my mom will stop
harassing Red's family.

215
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,267
Right?

216
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:07,800
And I think everything
will be okay now.

217
00:15:07,933 --> 00:15:09,600
We'll be at peace.

218
00:15:11,333 --> 00:15:13,767
It's possible.

219
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:15,600
And who would have thought

220
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,100
that your mom
would finally accept

221
00:15:17,233 --> 00:15:19,067
your relationship with Red?

222
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:21,500
You and Red!

223
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:25,533
I can't wait to see Red.

224
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:27,767
I want to see how he's doing.

225
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,867
He's doing okay.

226
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,400
I checked on him. I dropped by.

227
00:15:32,533 --> 00:15:33,733
He's doing great.

228
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:36,100
So get better.

229
00:15:36,267 --> 00:15:39,567
Get your strength back,
and you will see him soon, okay?

230
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,867
How soon is soon?
I want to see him now.

231
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,233
- What?
- Help me up.

232
00:15:43,367 --> 00:15:45,067
Come on. Let's go see him.

233
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,067
What?

234
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,367
Come on!

235
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:21,200
Lucho.

236
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:25,500
What does this video mean?

237
00:16:26,967 --> 00:16:28,667
Don't you still get it, Victor?

238
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:32,900
Your son got in an accident

239
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,233
because of what your wife
and her brother did.

240
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:39,367
Rina told Zandro

241
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:42,900
to cut my car's brake line

242
00:16:43,067 --> 00:16:45,033
to get Amanda and me
in an accident.

243
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:48,267
But your son ended up
getting hurt because of it.

244
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:55,400
No, no, no.

245
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,400
Rina is not capable
of doing this.

246
00:17:02,033 --> 00:17:04,833
She hid all her illegal business
from you before.

247
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,167
You don't know
a lot of horrible things...

248
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:10,633
that Rina can do.

249
00:17:16,667 --> 00:17:18,367
We got into an accident...

250
00:17:19,567 --> 00:17:21,200
because the car's brake
didn't work.

251
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:36,333
Rina, is it true?

252
00:17:36,467 --> 00:17:38,733
You had something to do
with our son's accident?

253
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:41,733
Did he say something?

254
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:45,367
And you believe him?

255
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:48,533
Here's the proof, Rina.

256
00:17:57,067 --> 00:17:59,667
Eden, are you sure about this?

257
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,700
His mom might not let us in.

258
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:03,667
Mommy Rina likes me.

259
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:04,967
We won't have a problem
with her.

260
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:08,767
Hey, where are you going?

261
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,967
We're going to see Red, Mom.

262
00:18:12,533 --> 00:18:14,300
Eden. I won't stop you
from seeing him,

263
00:18:14,433 --> 00:18:16,533
but not right now.
You won't like what you'll see

264
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:18,100
if you go there.

265
00:18:20,433 --> 00:18:22,467
What do you mean?
I don't understand.

266
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:31,433
Obviously,
that's a fabricated video.

267
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:33,067
Come on,
that's been tampered with.

268
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:35,000
That's not true, Victor.

269
00:18:35,133 --> 00:18:37,433
This video looks clear to me.

270
00:18:37,567 --> 00:18:38,800
This is Zandro.

271
00:18:40,967 --> 00:18:42,100
It could be Zandro.

272
00:18:42,233 --> 00:18:45,267
But do we know
who told him to do that?

273
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,500
No, right?

274
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:50,833
And besides, it's been a while
since I heard from him.

275
00:18:50,967 --> 00:18:54,133
I overheard you on your phone
the other night.

276
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:56,733
You were talking to Zandro.

277
00:18:56,867 --> 00:19:00,633
Don't you dare rat me out!

278
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:03,067
Who are you talking to?

279
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,867
I ordered something online.

280
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:15,900
They called me about the product
I had reserved.

281
00:19:16,033 --> 00:19:17,800
I told them to call me
some other time.

282
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:18,967
I'm busy now.

283
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,800
You're still lying to me?

284
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:28,600
What do you mean?
How is Mommy Rina to blame

285
00:19:28,767 --> 00:19:30,733
for our accident?

286
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,133
How did that happen?

287
00:19:32,267 --> 00:19:35,267
Zandro confessed
that Rina told him

288
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:40,800
to cut the brake line
of our car.

289
00:19:42,533 --> 00:19:45,800
I don't think they're capable
of doing that, Mom.

290
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:47,633
Here.

291
00:19:47,767 --> 00:19:53,167
This is the CCTV footage.

292
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:56,233
Zandro did it.

293
00:19:56,367 --> 00:19:58,967
He cut the brake line
of our car.

294
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:01,933
And the result
of the investigation

295
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,233
says the same.

296
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:07,267
Rina told him to do it.

297
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:15,733
Mom, I'm sorry.

298
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:22,767
I'm sorry, but Rina
doesn't really care about you.

299
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:25,300
She doesn't like you for Red.

300
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:29,000
She only wants to use you
to get revenge.

301
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,667
I don't know you anymore!

302
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:39,967
You're no longer the woman
I married.

303
00:20:41,467 --> 00:20:43,067
And I can't believe

304
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,300
you're capable
of hurting other people.

305
00:20:47,133 --> 00:20:50,500
And because you were obsessed
with hurting Eden and Amanda,

306
00:20:50,633 --> 00:20:52,100
you harmed our son too.

307
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:55,100
I don't know
if I can forgive you.

308
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:56,200
Victor...

309
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,533
Victor, wait.

310
00:20:58,667 --> 00:21:01,067
- Okay, let me...
- Don't come near me, Rina.

311
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:04,733
- Victor.
- I don't know

312
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:06,300
if I can forgive you.

313
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:08,733
Enough!

314
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:20,767
You're the reason...

315
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:25,333
Yenyen and me had an accident?

316
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:33,667
I promised God
that I'd let go of my hatred.

317
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:34,733
But this...

318
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:38,567
I have the evidence now.

319
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,100
I can't let this slide.

320
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:47,467
Mom, I'm sorry.

321
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:51,133
I'm sorry for believing them
over you.

322
00:21:51,267 --> 00:21:53,633
I'm sorry, Mom. They're so evil.

323
00:21:53,767 --> 00:21:55,500
It's okay.
Let's put it behind us.

324
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:57,400
What matters now
is that you're safe.

325
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:00,433
Don't go there for now.

326
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,400
I'm sorry.

327
00:22:04,533 --> 00:22:05,900
It's okay.

328
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:13,367
You're the reason
we had an accident?

329
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:17,333
No, Red. Okay, listen to me.

330
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:25,433
Obviously,
they're accusing me again.

331
00:22:25,567 --> 00:22:30,000
Eden's family is just doing this
to ruin us.

332
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:31,167
They're just accusing me.

333
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:32,433
- It's not true.
- That's enough.

334
00:22:32,567 --> 00:22:33,567
That's enough, Mom.

335
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:34,667
Stop it, Mom.

336
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:39,200
- It's not true, Red.
- I don't want to hear it!

337
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,267
The CCTV footage can't lie.

338
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,167
And Miss Amanda is not lying.

339
00:22:49,533 --> 00:22:50,500
It's you!

340
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:52,967
You're the one who's lying.

341
00:22:55,533 --> 00:22:57,233
Victor, explain it to him.

342
00:22:57,367 --> 00:22:59,400
It's not my fault, right?

343
00:22:59,533 --> 00:23:00,800
Victor.

344
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:01,900
Victor.

345
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:12,700
Excuse me, we have a warrant
of arrest for Mrs. Rina Ramos.

346
00:23:12,833 --> 00:23:14,533
I won't come with you!

347
00:23:14,667 --> 00:23:16,400
- Victor!
- Sorry, Rina. Go!

348
00:23:16,533 --> 00:23:17,433
- Red.
- Go!

349
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:19,167
- You have to go.
- Victor!

350
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:22,433
Red, I thought
I wouldn't see you again.

351
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:24,167
I thought it was the end
of everything.

352
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,600
We survived the island.

353
00:23:25,733 --> 00:23:27,733
We survived our families' feud.

354
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:29,967
No one can break us apart.

355
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:31,500
Red!

356
00:23:31,633 --> 00:23:34,400
Red, help me.

357
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:36,800
Don't leave me, Red.

358
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:39,267
- Red!
- Should I drop the charges?

359
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:42,333
Rina has to learn her lesson.

360
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:43,967
Red and I accept it.

361
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,133
There you go.
Your make-up looks perfect now.

362
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:47,533
You can get dressed.
